WEBVTT

00:37.746 --> 00:39.077
[SIGHS]

00:41.125 --> 00:43.286
I'm sure there were moments...

00:43.460 --> 00:47.499
...when King Arthur regretted pulling
the sword from the stone.

00:48.132 --> 00:50.623
But he never gave up his quest.

00:51.218 --> 00:52.378
So why did you?

00:53.137 --> 00:55.173
Or have you already found the Traveler...

00:55.347 --> 00:59.465
...that you and the less fortunate members
of Veritas were looking for?

00:59.685 --> 01:01.095
The Traveler.

01:01.270 --> 01:05.639
Why doesn't it surprise me that you've
fallen for Patricia Swann's vivid imaginings?

01:05.816 --> 01:09.024
I didn't imagine the deaths of Virgil Swann
or Queen's parents.

01:09.194 --> 01:13.107
You think I can control the fate
of individuals? Oh, God.

01:13.907 --> 01:15.488
You give me too much credit.

01:15.659 --> 01:18.196
You certainly controlled mine.

01:19.413 --> 01:23.827
It wasn't an accident we were in Smallville
the day of the meteor shower, was it?

01:25.002 --> 01:27.334
The factory was just a cover.

01:27.838 --> 01:31.751
You were really there to meet this Traveler
that Veritas wanted to protect.

01:31.925 --> 01:34.541
-I remember everything, Dad.
-Those are the memories...

01:34.720 --> 01:39.009
...of a small boy in shock trying to cope
with the trauma of a meteor shower.

01:39.183 --> 01:41.094
A trauma brought on by my own father.

01:46.398 --> 01:49.265
My life changed forever that day.

01:56.867 --> 01:59.779
You sacriﬁced me for the Traveler.

02:02.206 --> 02:03.696
Why?

02:07.753 --> 02:09.539
Who is it, Dad?

02:11.298 --> 02:12.834
Who is it?

02:14.885 --> 02:16.421
Who is it?

02:19.181 --> 02:21.467
What if I told you now...

02:21.934 --> 02:23.970
...that you are the Traveler?

02:33.904 --> 02:36.566
You're right.
Your life truly changed that day.

02:36.740 --> 02:40.028
I told you in the helicopter that you
were destined for a great future.

02:40.202 --> 02:43.786
That's why I've been so hard on you,
trained you so relentlessly.

02:43.956 --> 02:45.696
Think, Lex. Think.

02:45.874 --> 02:48.490
You have survived mortal injuries
so many times.

02:48.669 --> 02:50.910
How else can you explain it?

02:53.924 --> 02:56.711
Because I was trained
never to accept defeat.

02:59.429 --> 03:02.296
When I get my hands on that box
in Zurich...

03:02.474 --> 03:05.261
...l have a feeling all my questions
will be answered.

03:18.991 --> 03:20.527
Lex?

03:22.202 --> 03:26.662
I know how strong it is,
the attraction of the dark power.

03:26.832 --> 03:28.743
But it will destroy you.

03:29.960 --> 03:33.498
I can't let you go down that terrible path.

03:35.215 --> 03:37.206
You must not open that box.

03:38.969 --> 03:43.178
I can't open it
because I need a second key.

03:44.016 --> 03:45.552
Give it to me.

03:51.273 --> 03:52.479
[GUN COCKS]

03:57.988 --> 04:01.526
I've swept every possible place
you could've hidden it...

04:02.659 --> 04:07.995
...and I ﬁnally realized, there's only
one person you would trust it with.

04:08.999 --> 04:10.034
Yourself.

04:10.208 --> 04:11.823
[FABRIC RIPS]

04:13.670 --> 04:15.001
Lex?

04:15.172 --> 04:19.165
Lex, if you open that box,
if you get hold of that secret...

04:20.177 --> 04:22.839
...there will be no redemption for you.
No redemption.

04:23.013 --> 04:24.549
Ever.

04:25.849 --> 04:28.511
I was raised in your shadow.

04:30.604 --> 04:32.640
Now you're gonna die in mine.

04:36.652 --> 04:39.394
No one will even remember your name.

04:40.030 --> 04:41.816
[LIONEL GRUNTS]

05:48.098 --> 05:49.588
[KEYBOARD CLICKING]

05:50.600 --> 05:53.728
CHLOE: I'm sorry, Clark. I traveled halfway
around the world via satellite.

05:53.895 --> 05:56.511
There's no trace of Kara and Brainiac.

05:56.690 --> 06:00.603
I can't let Lana sit in an asylum in pain.
The only way to help her is to ﬁnd Brainiac.

06:00.777 --> 06:03.154
I've tapped every radar screen
known to mankind.

06:03.321 --> 06:05.186
There's no bogey
or blip unaccounted for.

06:05.365 --> 06:07.651
It's like they just ﬂew off the map.

06:07.951 --> 06:10.363
What about Brainiac's power sources?

06:10.537 --> 06:13.529
Check the electrical grid
for any power surges again.

06:18.253 --> 06:20.039
[SIREN WAILING]

06:21.548 --> 06:23.379
Stay focused, Chloe.

06:24.259 --> 06:26.215
Busy night out there.

06:26.595 --> 06:28.131
MAN: I got--
MAN 2: Go and grab the kit.

06:28.305 --> 06:29.465
WOMAN: It's all right.
MAN 3: Got it.

06:29.639 --> 06:30.890
What's going on?

06:31.058 --> 06:33.140
Someone at LuthorCorp jumped out
their window.

06:33.310 --> 06:35.642
Rumor has it, it was Lionel Luthor.

06:40.567 --> 06:41.977
CHLOE:
Clark?

06:42.152 --> 06:43.642
Let's go.

06:52.287 --> 06:54.278
[SIRENS WAILING]

07:10.639 --> 07:12.630
[HELICOPTER WHIRRING,
INDISTINCT CHATTER]

07:12.808 --> 07:14.799
[RADIO CHATTER,
CAMERAS CLICKING]

07:23.860 --> 07:25.976
Ijust talked to him.

07:26.154 --> 07:29.237
You said you were working down the hall
from your father tonight?

07:32.536 --> 07:34.527
I heard him yell.

07:37.374 --> 07:39.239
Then he was gone.

07:40.001 --> 07:44.335
I know how difﬁcult this must be for you,
but I need a positive identiﬁcation.

07:47.300 --> 07:49.211
Whenever you're ready.

08:10.407 --> 08:11.567
Yeah.

08:11.741 --> 08:13.242
Thank you.

08:16.454 --> 08:18.194
MAN:
Mr. Luthor.

08:23.086 --> 08:24.587
[LEX PANTING]

08:31.428 --> 08:33.259
YOUNG LEX:
You killed him?

08:38.852 --> 08:41.218
You killed Dad.

08:49.446 --> 08:52.358
MAN:
Sir, do you want to make any statement?

09:08.173 --> 09:09.788
WOMAN:
Sir?

09:09.966 --> 09:11.831
Can you give a statement?

09:22.687 --> 09:28.057
Not that I wanna speak ill of the dead,
but Lionel left a lot of damage in his wake.

09:29.527 --> 09:31.358
He locked you in a kryptonite box.

09:31.529 --> 09:33.815
Lionel did a lot of things.
He'd never commit suicide.

09:33.990 --> 09:37.903
I don't know about that. He was beyond
disturbed when he came to the Daily Planet.

09:38.078 --> 09:42.037
It doesn't mean he'd take his own life.
He was rattled the last time I saw him.

09:42.207 --> 09:44.744
He was desperate to give me something,
a locket.

09:45.752 --> 09:50.337
What does a locket have to do with Lionel
falling 40 stories from his ofﬁce window?

10:19.244 --> 10:21.109
Mr. Luthor?

10:21.871 --> 10:25.910
I just wanted to tell you how sorry I was
to hear about your father.

10:31.798 --> 10:33.663
When I was a boy...

10:34.968 --> 10:38.552
...we took a trip together
to Washington, D.C., just--

10:39.180 --> 10:41.262
It was just the two of us.

10:44.060 --> 10:48.303
I thought I was just tagging along
on another business trip...

10:50.025 --> 10:53.267
...but he wanted to show me
the Air and Space Museum.

10:54.904 --> 10:57.737
He knew I loved things that could ﬂy.

11:01.077 --> 11:04.945
We were looking up
at the Apollo 11 Command Module.

11:06.583 --> 11:08.995
I couldn't believe it went to the moon.

11:11.379 --> 11:13.870
My father held my hand...

11:16.092 --> 11:18.583
...and he told me, "The right man...

11:19.512 --> 11:22.049
...can make anything possible."

11:37.781 --> 11:39.567
[EXHALES]

11:48.833 --> 11:50.209
You have his locket.

11:51.669 --> 11:54.251
How did you get him to--?

11:57.801 --> 11:59.166
Lex...

11:59.344 --> 12:01.585
...Lionel was a cruel, sadistic man.

12:05.975 --> 12:07.761
What are you suggesting?

12:09.104 --> 12:11.720
No one will ever know, Lex.

12:12.440 --> 12:14.305
I promise you.

12:31.334 --> 12:33.040
Where's the key?

12:35.630 --> 12:37.586
It was empty.

12:39.134 --> 12:42.171
My father must have given it
to someone.

12:44.139 --> 12:47.222
I asked you to keep an eye on him, Gina.

12:48.184 --> 12:50.015
[SETS LOCKET DOWN]

12:51.563 --> 12:54.430
Lionel stopped by the Daily Planet
before going to LuthorCorp.

12:54.607 --> 12:56.723
He was spotted in the basement.

13:00.655 --> 13:02.941
Get the helicopter ready.

13:04.451 --> 13:06.157
Of course.

13:12.333 --> 13:14.073
[DOOR CLOSES]

13:21.092 --> 13:24.209
YOUNG LEX:
You killed Dad for a necklace?

13:25.513 --> 13:27.344
You're not real.

13:34.230 --> 13:37.597
He was mean sometimes,
but he loved us, Lex.

13:37.775 --> 13:39.060
Get out of my head.

13:39.819 --> 13:41.320
Get out of my head!

13:41.488 --> 13:43.570
You shouldn't have done it!

13:44.657 --> 13:46.909
I had no choice!

13:48.161 --> 13:50.152
[PANTING]

14:10.391 --> 14:12.382
[SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE]

14:15.104 --> 14:17.095
[HELICOPTER WHIRRING]

14:32.455 --> 14:33.615
[DOOR UNLOCKS]

15:23.256 --> 15:26.248
"For Kal-El, in the event of my death."

15:41.899 --> 15:44.185
[DEVICE HUMMING]

15:56.122 --> 15:59.330
LIONEL: In my lifetime, I’ve known
many famous and powerful men:

15:59.500 --> 16:01.411
Presidents, sultans, kings...

16:01.586 --> 16:04.453
...and I believed that I was superior
to them all.

16:04.631 --> 16:06.747
But I've come to know the truth, Kal-EI.

16:06.924 --> 16:10.007
My greatest accomplishment
is that I have dedicated myself...

16:10.178 --> 16:12.715
...to protecting your life and serving you.

16:12.889 --> 16:14.220
For that, I am grateful.

16:14.390 --> 16:15.800
But if you are reading this...

16:15.975 --> 16:20.218
...it means that I cannot protect you
any longer from a terrible truth.

16:20.772 --> 16:22.933
Two lockets exist. Two.

16:23.107 --> 16:25.359
Each one has its own key.

16:25.526 --> 16:30.646
These keys, used together,
unlock the secret of controlling you.

16:31.741 --> 16:33.697
You must ﬁnd the keys, Kal-El...

16:33.868 --> 16:37.907
...or your destiny will fall
into the hands of another man.

16:38.206 --> 16:40.492
You must save yourself.

16:56.432 --> 17:00.300
What is it with the Luthors? I swear, death
follows that family like a stray puppy.

17:00.478 --> 17:03.766
-You'll not believe this--
-I wanted to search LuthorCorp tonight...

17:03.940 --> 17:06.272
...for evidence
that Lex had Patricia Swann killed.

17:06.442 --> 17:09.275
But you, no, genius that you are,
you wanted to stay here...

17:09.445 --> 17:12.061
...and search through meaningless memos
in Lex's ofﬁce.

17:12.240 --> 17:14.572
-Lois?
-While we were here at the Daily Planet...

17:14.742 --> 17:16.983
...photographing everything
but bottled water...

17:17.161 --> 17:19.903
...the story of a lifetime was happening
across the street.

17:20.081 --> 17:22.788
Lois, just take a look at the view.

17:22.959 --> 17:25.541
One of tonight's shots from Lex's ofﬁce.

17:26.921 --> 17:28.331
What?

17:29.465 --> 17:31.080
The schoolboy crush is sweet...

17:31.259 --> 17:33.841
...but you need to adjust your focus
in more ways.

17:34.011 --> 17:36.468
This is serious.
Bodies are falling out of the sky.

17:36.639 --> 17:38.504
And we have the picture to prove it.

17:38.683 --> 17:42.301
-Lex's ofﬁce looks out over LuthorCorp.
-And?

17:42.478 --> 17:43.467
[SIGHS]

17:46.983 --> 17:48.974
It's Lionel Luthor right before he died.

17:49.152 --> 17:50.312
What?

17:50.486 --> 17:52.101
No way.

17:53.239 --> 17:54.775
Creepy.

17:54.949 --> 17:57.065
I can't believe you got this, Jimmy.

17:57.243 --> 17:59.484
Well, it's gonna get creepier.

18:00.329 --> 18:01.318
[KEYBOARD CLICKING]

18:02.331 --> 18:04.492
There's someone else in the room.

18:05.668 --> 18:07.408
Lionel Luthor might have been pushed.

18:08.004 --> 18:10.996
You think this blurry blob of pixels
is the killer? Come on.

18:11.340 --> 18:12.329
Trust me.

18:12.508 --> 18:15.750
This has Pulitzer written it all over it.

18:16.345 --> 18:19.428
Yeah? What are you waiting for?
Sharpen the shot.

18:20.183 --> 18:23.596
Well, it's not that easy.
My computer's not powerful enough.

18:25.521 --> 18:29.935
Hey, what about that heavy-duty hardware
that Lana's stashed at the Isis Foundation?

18:30.359 --> 18:31.974
Nice.

18:32.361 --> 18:34.773
I can upload this bad boy
to the foundation's server.

18:34.947 --> 18:36.357
If we're on Lana's system...

18:36.532 --> 18:39.615
...we could probably use Chloe's mad skills
with a CPU.

18:40.244 --> 18:42.951
Oh, that is,
if we can pry her away from Clark.

18:43.122 --> 18:45.363
Chloe and I share the same DNA.

18:45.541 --> 18:48.499
Trust me, Jimmy.
She's gonna wanna be in on this.

19:17.657 --> 19:18.988
[KEY CLINKS]

19:36.384 --> 19:37.874
[SHREDDER WHIRRING]

19:43.641 --> 19:45.177
Lex.

19:46.853 --> 19:48.764
I'm so sorry about your father.

19:50.606 --> 19:52.437
Thank you, Chloe.

19:53.734 --> 19:55.941
He visited you here tonight.

19:56.320 --> 19:59.437
Yeah, he really wasn't himself.

19:59.866 --> 20:01.697
I fear, in his deluded state of mind...

20:01.868 --> 20:05.360
...my father disposed
of some valuable family heirlooms.

20:05.538 --> 20:07.119
Did he give you anything?

20:09.834 --> 20:14.077
CHLOE: Other than the feeling
that something was deﬁnitely off? No.

20:14.255 --> 20:17.463
He was only here for a few minutes.
To be honest, I got scared so I—

20:17.633 --> 20:19.498
Have you checked your desk?

20:22.889 --> 20:26.928
He didn't give me anything, Lex.
I swear he just came here to talk.

20:39.280 --> 20:41.487
This was my father's.

20:43.659 --> 20:46.116
I've never seen it before.

20:47.580 --> 20:51.289
-Why were you hiding it from me?
-If I knew it was yours, I wouldn't keep it.

20:51.459 --> 20:53.996
Why would he even give it to you?

20:55.212 --> 20:57.294
Do you know what this key is for?

20:58.341 --> 21:01.208
Lex, Lionel wasn't in his right mind
when he was here.

21:01.385 --> 21:04.343
I don't know why he left that.

21:05.848 --> 21:07.588
You're ﬁred.

21:10.770 --> 21:12.101
[DOOR OPENS]

21:13.439 --> 21:16.351
Escort Miss Sullivan from the building.

21:16.859 --> 21:20.568
CHLOE: Aren't you gonna give me a second
to clear out my private things?

21:22.031 --> 21:24.522
Your personal items will be boxed up
and sent to your home.

21:28.663 --> 21:33.532
If anything is missing, Lex, I swear to God,
you won't hear the end of it.

21:38.297 --> 21:40.413
I'll pack up Miss Sullivan's belongings.

21:40.591 --> 21:42.001
You go back to the mansion.

21:42.176 --> 21:43.461
Get some sleep.

21:47.556 --> 21:48.716
We did it, Lex.

22:02.738 --> 22:04.729
[DOOR OPENS, GINA SIGHS]

22:06.492 --> 22:07.652
[DOOR CLOSES]

22:11.497 --> 22:13.203
[CELL PHONE VIBRATING]

22:19.380 --> 22:20.916
[CELL PHONE BEEPING]

22:29.265 --> 22:31.381
LOIS:
Okay, that's it. I'm leaving.

22:31.559 --> 22:33.515
I wanna start working on this picture...

22:33.686 --> 22:36.803
...but we haven't heard from Chloe yet.
I think that we should wait.

22:36.981 --> 22:38.767
News waits for no one, not even Chloe.

22:38.941 --> 22:42.183
You texted her, you left her three voicemail
messages at the apartment.

22:42.361 --> 22:45.273
She's not Helen Keller.
She'll get the message, meet us there.

22:45.448 --> 22:47.359
It wouldn't kill us to wait a few...

22:47.825 --> 22:49.861
...more minutes.

22:50.369 --> 22:52.234
I agree with Mr. Olsen.

23:00.004 --> 23:01.164
[DOOR OPENS]

23:01.338 --> 23:05.001
JIMMY: Why are we outside of the kitchen?
It's a little late for a snack, isn't it?

23:05.176 --> 23:07.713
LOIS: I've seen you here before, haven't I?
You work for Lex.

23:07.887 --> 23:09.718
GINA:
Mr. Luthor has nothing to do with this.

23:09.889 --> 23:12.301
I'm here about that photograph you took.

23:12.475 --> 23:15.342
Which photograph would that be?
I take a whole lot of pictures.

23:15.519 --> 23:19.182
Lionel in his ofﬁce before he killed himself.
I want that photo destroyed.

23:19.356 --> 23:22.814
His death was tragic enough without it
being sensationalized by the media.

23:22.985 --> 23:25.727
You could have said that
before you broke out the artillery.

23:25.905 --> 23:28.521
As soon as we saw it,
I jumped on the delete button.

23:28.699 --> 23:30.564
This is all a big, big misunderstanding.

23:30.743 --> 23:31.858
You're lying.

23:32.036 --> 23:33.492
I deleted it.

23:34.997 --> 23:36.328
After I saw your message...

23:36.499 --> 23:39.411
...I went into the mainframe
and pulled it from your hard drive.

23:39.585 --> 23:42.668
The transfer log shows you uploaded
the ﬁle to a second server...

23:42.838 --> 23:46.831
...with a cloaked IP address.
I wanna know where you sent it.

23:51.013 --> 23:52.844
[LOIS GRUNTING]

23:54.517 --> 23:57.099
-You shot me?
-You weren't cooperating.

23:57.520 --> 24:00.978
-How about a warning?
-Tell me or she dies. Where's the server?

24:02.983 --> 24:06.817
It's the Isis Foundation. It's 3rd
and Broadway. It's a 10-minute drive.

24:19.542 --> 24:22.033
I'll come back for you when I'm done.

24:22.878 --> 24:23.867
[DOOR LOCKS]

24:27.550 --> 24:28.539
[LOIS GROANS]

24:28.717 --> 24:30.127
You're really bleeding, Lois.

24:33.973 --> 24:35.463
[LOIS GROANING]

24:40.396 --> 24:43.763
I guess trying to take on
one of Lex Luthor's fembots...

24:43.941 --> 24:47.149
...doesn't make me the smartest icicle
in the freezer.

24:51.574 --> 24:52.689
Don't worry.

24:52.867 --> 24:54.653
I'm gonna get us out of here.

25:03.169 --> 25:06.081
Hey, is anyone out there?

25:11.010 --> 25:12.591
Hey!

25:12.970 --> 25:15.052
Is anyone in there?

25:15.431 --> 25:16.716
Help!

25:16.891 --> 25:18.973
Can anyone hear me?

25:27.985 --> 25:29.941
-Hey.
-Hey. Jimmy and Lois here?

25:30.112 --> 25:32.694
Not yet, but Jimmy's message said
he sent the ﬁles...

25:32.865 --> 25:34.730
...so I was about to get started.

25:36.493 --> 25:39.621
I got a message that Lionel left for me
in his vault.

25:39.788 --> 25:42.245
Chloe, I think I know why he was killed.

25:43.250 --> 25:44.786
He was trying to protect me.

25:46.587 --> 25:48.794
Lionel did say something terrible
was coming.

25:48.964 --> 25:51.626
There's something on Earth
that can be used to control me.

25:51.800 --> 25:54.382
Control you? As in "do my bidding,"
some sort of puppet?

25:54.553 --> 25:56.635
I mean, what could possibly pull
your strings?

25:56.805 --> 26:00.093
I don't know. But whatever it is,
it takes two keys to unlock.

26:01.060 --> 26:03.551
Clark, when I went back
to the Daily Planet tonight...

26:03.729 --> 26:05.139
...there was a key in my desk.

26:05.314 --> 26:07.020
Lionel left it there for you.

26:07.191 --> 26:08.271
Where is it?

26:08.651 --> 26:09.811
Lex took it.

26:09.985 --> 26:13.443
I was trying to hide it from him,
but then he ﬁred me.

26:13.614 --> 26:17.152
Which is ﬁne because I wanted to get out
of that black hole anyway, but--

26:17.326 --> 26:19.658
We don't have time
to talk about my 9-to-5.

26:19.828 --> 26:23.195
So you think that that mystery man
was after the locket?

26:23.374 --> 26:26.411
I don't think our mystery man
is much of a mystery at all...

26:26.585 --> 26:30.578
...considering Lex went to the Daily Planet,
the same night that his father died...

26:30.756 --> 26:33.088
...and ﬁred you over that key.

26:33.634 --> 26:36.296
How long till we get an ID
on this picture?

26:36.679 --> 26:39.341
Jimmy said there isn't a lot of photo
in this photograph.

26:39.515 --> 26:41.426
It'll take me at least a couple of hours.

26:41.809 --> 26:43.015
Keep working on it.

26:43.185 --> 26:44.345
[WHOOSHING]

26:49.483 --> 26:50.814
[SIGHS]

27:20.055 --> 27:22.888
My father just died
and you're already breaking and entering?

27:23.225 --> 27:25.557
Lionel would never take his own life.

27:28.272 --> 27:31.890
I thought you'd at least try
to offer some words of comfort.

27:32.234 --> 27:33.735
Get out.

27:33.902 --> 27:36.154
I'm not going anywhere.

27:36.989 --> 27:38.729
YOUNG LEX:
You can still be good, Lex.

27:38.907 --> 27:40.647
Tell Clark what you did.

27:40.826 --> 27:41.861
He's our friend.

27:42.036 --> 27:45.073
I'm not gonna debate
my father's mental state with you.

27:46.874 --> 27:50.207
I'm grieving, Clark. I think you know
what it's like to lose a father.

27:51.128 --> 27:52.834
Don't bring my father into this.

27:53.839 --> 27:55.579
Why not?

27:56.633 --> 27:58.919
Our fathers were a lot alike.

27:59.094 --> 28:03.428
Smart, strong-willed
and both died prematurely.

28:06.518 --> 28:08.474
You know, you're right, Lex.

28:09.021 --> 28:11.228
Lionel did die too soon.

28:11.523 --> 28:13.388
I wanna know the truth
about how he died.

28:13.776 --> 28:15.858
The truth is...

28:16.236 --> 28:18.192
...our dads were alike in another way.

28:22.034 --> 28:26.619
See, they both felt that you were
the kind of son a father could be proud of.

28:27.122 --> 28:29.784
He would have felt the same way
about you, Lex...

28:29.958 --> 28:32.119
...if you would have tried.

28:32.920 --> 28:34.581
What happened to you?

28:35.631 --> 28:37.792
I did try, Clark.

28:38.967 --> 28:41.344
In fact, when we ﬁrst met...

28:41.845 --> 28:43.927
...you inspired me.

28:44.556 --> 28:47.013
All I wanted was to be your friend...

28:47.184 --> 28:48.970
...but you turned your back on me.

28:51.063 --> 28:54.055
So you're the person you are today
because of me.

28:55.859 --> 28:58.271
I tried to be your friend, Lex.

28:58.695 --> 29:02.688
-But all you care about is power and control.
-This is Smallville!

29:03.033 --> 29:07.276
Meteor freaks, alien ships,
cryptic symbols.

29:07.496 --> 29:09.157
These threats are real.

29:09.331 --> 29:10.832
Someone had to take control.

29:10.999 --> 29:12.660
Someone has to protect the world.

29:12.835 --> 29:14.621
Listen to yourself, Lex.

29:14.795 --> 29:18.708
You're so caught up in your own delusions,
you've lost track of reality.

29:19.007 --> 29:20.668
Have I?

29:21.885 --> 29:25.002
Then let's talk about something
you can't deny.

29:26.014 --> 29:30.428
After years of pleading with my father
to show me some compassion...

29:31.019 --> 29:32.850
...he turned to you...

29:33.021 --> 29:35.148
...with open arms.

29:35.774 --> 29:39.062
Now, what would a worldly billionaire
have in common...

29:39.236 --> 29:41.522
...with a simple farm boy?

29:43.282 --> 29:45.944
Maybe he just knew he could trust me.

29:46.952 --> 29:48.112
[SCOFFS]

29:48.787 --> 29:50.652
Of course.

29:51.290 --> 29:54.202
Everyone can trust Clark Kent.

29:54.751 --> 29:57.037
You're the perfect son.

29:58.547 --> 30:04.213
So-- So why did Jonathan Kent
always seem so stressed?

30:05.179 --> 30:09.218
I mean, was raising the perfect son
really that much work?

30:10.684 --> 30:13.471
I wonder how much of a strain
it put on his heart.

30:15.898 --> 30:19.061
Are you blaming me
for my father's death?

30:19.401 --> 30:20.641
Are you?

30:22.905 --> 30:24.896
You're the guilty one, Lex, not me.

30:25.073 --> 30:27.985
And this time, you're gonna own up
to what you've done.

30:28.994 --> 30:30.530
I know you killed Lionel.

30:31.538 --> 30:32.698
[SCOFFS]

30:33.665 --> 30:37.078
-Who's delusional now?
-I have proof.

30:45.677 --> 30:46.837
[SNIFFS]

30:57.648 --> 30:59.138
[KEYBOARD CLICKING]

31:11.119 --> 31:12.620
[STATIC HISSING]

31:16.917 --> 31:19.124
You really did it, Lex.

31:31.139 --> 31:32.640
[MONITORS BEEPING]

31:45.862 --> 31:47.477
CLARK:
Chloe?

31:53.203 --> 31:54.704
Chloe?

31:55.497 --> 31:57.283
Chloe, you in here?

31:57.457 --> 31:58.833
Chloe, what happened?

31:59.001 --> 32:01.083
-You okay?
-Somebody hit me.

32:01.253 --> 32:03.665
-Here.
-Clark?

32:04.923 --> 32:07.505
[SIGHING]
They destroyed the picture.

32:08.010 --> 32:09.420
But you were right, Clark.

32:09.595 --> 32:11.506
I saw the picture. It was Lex.

32:13.765 --> 32:15.630
When I went to see Lex,
I found Lionel's locket.

32:15.809 --> 32:18.721
But without that photograph,
we can't prove anything.

32:18.895 --> 32:20.886
-What about the key?
-I x-rayed the mansion.

32:21.064 --> 32:22.929
It's nowhere to be found.

32:24.026 --> 32:27.814
-What happened to Jimmy and Lois?
-I don't know and I'm worried.

32:27.988 --> 32:29.774
They were leaving the Daily Planet.

32:29.948 --> 32:32.860
If whoever attacked me
followed the photo from there to here--

32:33.035 --> 32:36.903
He may have stopped Jimmy and Lois
from leaving the building. I gotta go.

32:37.080 --> 32:41.824
Clark, if Lex has both of those keys,
not only will he discover your secret...

32:42.002 --> 32:45.335
...but he'll have total
and complete power over you.

32:47.799 --> 32:52.668
Now that's not just your worst nightmare,
it's everyone else's too.

32:53.347 --> 32:54.553
Be careful.

32:59.353 --> 33:00.684
[WHOOSHING]

33:09.863 --> 33:11.023
[JIMMY SIGHS]

33:12.199 --> 33:14.906
JIMMY:
I've got an exclusive for you.

33:16.244 --> 33:18.326
When we get out of here...

33:20.582 --> 33:22.447
...Lois Lane...

33:22.626 --> 33:25.789
...and Jimmy Olsen
are gonna be world famous.

33:37.057 --> 33:39.514
JIMMY: We really do make a good team,
you know?

33:39.685 --> 33:44.429
I think there '8 gonna be plenty
of headlines ahead of us, I can see it now.

33:44.606 --> 33:46.562
It's gonna be great, Lois.

33:48.860 --> 33:50.566
[WHOOSHING]

34:14.636 --> 34:15.967
[WHOOSHING]

34:34.531 --> 34:36.271
[CELL PHONE BEEPING]

34:36.450 --> 34:37.610
[LINE RINGING]

34:37.784 --> 34:39.820
Hi, Lex. It's Gina.

34:39.995 --> 34:41.826
Please call me back.

34:41.997 --> 34:44.579
I found who you've been searching for.

34:44.750 --> 34:47.162
I know who the Traveler is.

34:47.753 --> 34:48.913
[CELL PHONE BEEPS]

34:54.384 --> 34:55.885
[GINA GASPING]

35:25.207 --> 35:27.198
[CAR CHIMING]

35:52.943 --> 35:56.435
After the funeral,
I plan on taking some time off.

35:56.738 --> 35:58.694
Get the jet ready.

35:59.699 --> 36:01.314
Zurich.

36:08.083 --> 36:09.414
[SIGHS]

36:11.253 --> 36:13.744
YOUNG LEX:
You can't run away, Lex.

36:14.339 --> 36:17.081
No matter where you go,
I'll always be there.

36:20.178 --> 36:22.169
You can't get rid of me.

36:24.266 --> 36:25.847
You need my help.

36:26.017 --> 36:29.601
There's still good inside you. I know it.

36:31.565 --> 36:33.601
I don't want your help.

36:33.984 --> 36:36.600
Don't go to Zurich.

36:38.780 --> 36:40.486
I'm going.

36:41.241 --> 36:42.447
I have to.

36:42.617 --> 36:44.357
Dad was right.

36:47.414 --> 36:49.905
If you open the box, it will destroy you.

36:50.667 --> 36:53.249
It's all I have left.

36:54.254 --> 36:55.790
It's not true.

37:00.135 --> 37:02.342
You still have me.

37:06.641 --> 37:08.142
No.

37:09.060 --> 37:11.972
I'm done listening to you.

37:13.148 --> 37:15.389
[YOUNG LEX GRUNTING]

37:25.702 --> 37:28.409
You make me weak.

38:17.045 --> 38:18.706
Long night.

38:20.173 --> 38:22.505
It's good to see the sun again.

38:23.843 --> 38:26.630
It's too bad Lionel's not here to see it.

38:28.306 --> 38:31.890
Lex closed the funeral
to any and all guests.

38:32.060 --> 38:35.552
In other words,
Lex is the only one invited.

38:42.362 --> 38:44.444
Lionel deserves better.

38:45.991 --> 38:48.949
At least we know
how Lionel truly felt about you.

38:49.119 --> 38:52.407
I mean, he thought of you
as his second son.

38:53.581 --> 38:56.539
Another person who treated me like a son
and died because of it.

38:57.419 --> 39:00.832
-Clark—
-Jor-El died getting me on that ship.

39:01.840 --> 39:06.004
My dad died of a heart attack
from the powers he took on protecting me.

39:07.262 --> 39:10.595
And now Lionel's been murdered
for protecting my secret.

39:13.601 --> 39:15.683
They did die for you, Clark.

39:15.854 --> 39:18.596
But ultimately, they died for all of us.

39:19.566 --> 39:21.727
There was a reason those men
were in your life.

39:21.901 --> 39:24.859
Each of them added something
to the man that you are today.

39:26.906 --> 39:29.113
How could Lex have done it?

39:30.118 --> 39:32.029
How does a son...

39:32.620 --> 39:34.451
...murder his own father?

39:36.624 --> 39:39.331
Total absence of love.

39:43.423 --> 39:45.960
Some say that's the deﬁnition of evil.

39:48.470 --> 39:53.385
You have to get those keys away from Lex,
Clark, before he kills anyone else.

39:56.144 --> 39:58.476
He's not gonna have the chance.

40:01.066 --> 40:02.772
I won't let him.

42:20.288 --> 42:22.279
[ENGLISH SDH]
